subSubSection.paragraph:
Abdomen
. Tergite 8 with posterior margin rounded (
Fig. 48
); sternite 8 with posterior margin rounded (
Fig. 51
); tergite 9 with short ventral struts (
Fig. 55
); sternite 9 with posterior margin truncate and with two pairs of long setae (
Fig. 44
); tergite 10 at posterior margin somewhat truncate, weakly pigmented, with short fringes and four setae on each side (
Fig. 55
). Median lobe of aedeagus with bulbous base and apex slightly rounded in ventral view and curved shape in lateral view, with apex curved (
Figs. 59–60
).

Female
. Similar to male except for: antennae shorter, scape without prominent tooth on inner face and without the longest setae on antennomeres 3, 5, 7, 9 and 11 (
Fig. 26
); abdominal sternite 8 with posterior margin slightly pointed and with short setae (
Fig. 75
); tergite 9 without ventral struts; tergite 10 wider at apex (
Fig. 83
) bursa copulatrix rounded (
Fig. 83
); ovipositor consisting of a pair of weakly pigmented hemisternites and a pair of more apical coxites, and with many long setae on apex (
Fig. 45
); spermatheca as 
Fig. 84
.
